{
  "info": {
    "name": "OTP Hora Backend API",
    "description": "Collection pour tester l'API OTP Hora (Express + Prisma).\n\n**Prérequis**\n- `base_url` : URL du serveur (ex. `https://otp-hora.onrender.com/api`).\n- `api_key` : clé API B2B (hash bcrypt), renvoyée en clair lors de `POST /enterprises` ou `POST /enterprises/register`.\n- `access_token` / `refresh_token` : utilisateur OTP Hora (`POST /users`, `POST /users/login`).\n- `company_access_token` / `company_refresh_token` : application entreprise (`POST /enterprises/login` ou inscription `POST /enterprises/register`).\n\n**Auth partenaire** : routes `links`, `auth/*` (serveur) acceptent `x-api-key` **ou** `Authorization: Bearer` avec un token **entreprise** (`role: company`).\n\n**Flux recommandé**\n1. Entreprise : `POST /enterprises/register` (nom + téléphone E.164 + PIN).\n2. Utilisateur : `POST /users` ou `POST /users/login` → tokens.\n3. `POST /devices` : **Bearer utilisateur** obligatoire ; `POST /enterprises/me/devices` : Bearer entreprise.\n4. Déverrouillage session PIN : `POST /users/session/unlock` ou `POST /enterprises/session/unlock` avec `refresh_token` + PIN.\n5. Historique connexions : `GET /users/me/login-history`, `GET /enterprises/me/login-history`.\n6. Liaison : `POST /links` → `POST /links/confirm` → `auth/request` → approve/reject.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "_postman_id": "otp-hora-backend-v1"
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "base_url", "value": "https://otp-hora.onrender.com/api" },
    { "key": "api_key", "value": "" },
    { "key": "user_id", "value": "" },
    { "key": "contact_id", "value": "" },
    { "key": "device_id", "value": "" },
    { "key": "enterprise_id", "value": "" },
    { "key": "link_id", "value": "" },
    { "key": "auth_request_id", "value": "" },
    { "key": "recovery_id", "value": "" },
    { "key": "external_ref", "value": "ext-user-001" },
    { "key": "access_token", "value": "" },
    { "key": "refresh_token", "value": "" },
    { "key": "company_access_token", "value": "" },
    { "key": "company_refresh_token", "value": "" }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "health",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "[OTP HORA] GET Health",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": "{{base_url}}/health",
            "description": "Vérifie que l'API répond (réponse texte brut, pas JSON)."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
                  "pm.test('Body contains running', function () {",
                  "  pm.expect(pm.response.text()).to.include('running');",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "enterprise_accounts",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "[ENTREPRISE] POST Register (téléphone + PIN)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"nom_entreprise\": \"Ma Société CI\",\n  \"phone\": \"+2250700000000\",\n  \"pin\": \"123456\"\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{base_url}}/enterprises/register",
            "description": "Inscription entreprise avec numéro international (E.164). Réponse 201 : `data` (profil), `api_key` (B2B), `auth` (access + refresh tokens entreprise). Exemple erreur : `PHONE_ALREADY_REGISTERED` (409)."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "[ENTREPRISE] POST Login (téléphone + PIN)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"phone\": \"+2250700000000\",\n  \"pin\": \"123456\"\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{base_url}}/enterprises/login",
            "description": "Connexion application entreprise. Réponse 200 : `data` + `auth` (Bearer). En-têtes optionnels : `User-Agent`, `X-Device-Name` pour l'historique."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "try {",
                  "  const j = pm.response.json();",
                  "  if (j.auth && j.auth.access_token) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('company_access_token', j.auth.access_token);",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('company_refresh_token', j.auth.refresh_token);",
                  "  }",
                  "} catch (e) {}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "[ENTREPRISE] POST Refresh token",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"refresh_token\": \"{{company_refresh_token}}\"\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{base_url}}/enterprises/refresh-token",
            "description": "Renouvelle les tokens JWT entreprise (refresh token avec role company)."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "[ENTREPRISE] POST Session unlock (PIN seulement)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"refresh_token\": \"{{company_refresh_token}}\",\n  \"pin\": \"123456\"\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{base_url}}/enterprises/session/unlock",
            "description": "Après retour sur l'app : vérifie le PIN avec le refresh token valide, réémet access + refresh. Exemple erreur : `INVALID_PIN` (401)."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "[ENTREPRISE] GET Me (profil, appareils, liens, historique)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{company_access_token}}" }
            ],
            "url": "{{base_url}}/enterprises/me",
            "description": "Profil entreprise authentifié par JWT : téléphone masqué côté logique liste dans `phone_e164`, `devices`, `linked_users`, `login_history` (5 dernières avec `label` formaté FR)."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "[ENTREPRISE] PATCH Me (nom, téléphone, PIN)",
          "request": {
